verses.text: Then sang Deborah and Barak the son of Abinoam on that day , saying ,
Praise ye the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* for the avenging of Israel , when the people willingly offered themselves.

Hear , O ye kings ; give ear , O ye princes ; I, \add even\add* I, will sing unto the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*; I will sing \add praise\add* to the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* God of Israel.
\nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, when thou wentest out of Seir , when thou marchedst out of the field of Edom , the earth trembled , and the heavens dropped , the clouds also dropped water.

The mountains melted from before the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, \add even\add* that Sinai from before the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* God of Israel.  +  r 5.5  t melted: Heb. flowed * \p

In the days of Shamgar the son of Anath , in the days of Jael , the highways were unoccupied , and the travellers walked through byways.\f + \fr 5.6 \ft travellers: Heb. walkers of paths\f*\f + \fr 5.6 \ft byways: Heb. crooked ways\f*
\add The inhabitants of\add* the villages ceased , they ceased in Israel , until that I Deborah arose , that I arose a mother in Israel.
They chose new gods ; then \add was\add* war in the gates : was there a shield or spear seen among forty thousand in Israel ?
My heart \add is\add* toward the governors of Israel , that offered themselves willingly among the people. Bless ye the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*.
Speak , ye that ride on white asses , ye that sit in judgment , and walk by the way.\f + \fr 5.10 \ft Speak: or, Meditate\f*

\add They that are delivered\add* from the noise of archers in the places of drawing water , there shall they rehearse the righteous acts of the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, \add even\add* the righteous acts \add toward the inhabitants\add* of his villages in Israel : then shall the people of the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* go down to the gates.  +  r 5.11  t righteous…: Heb. righteousnesses * \p
Awake , awake , Deborah : awake , awake , utter a song : arise , Barak , and lead thy captivity captive , thou son of Abinoam.
Then he made him that remaineth have dominion over the nobles among the people : the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* made me have dominion over the mighty.

Out of Ephraim \add was there\add* a root of them against Amalek ; after thee, Benjamin , among thy people ; out of Machir came down governors , and out of Zebulun they that handle the pen of the writer.\f + \fr 5.14 \ft handle: Heb. draw with\f*

And the princes of Issachar \add were\add* with Deborah ; even Issachar , and also Barak : he was sent on foot into the valley. For the divisions of Reuben \add there were\add* great thoughts of heart.\f + \fr 5.15 \ft foot: Heb. his feet\f*\f + \fr 5.15 \ft thoughts: Heb. impressions\f*\f + \fr 5.15 \ft For: or, In\f*
Why abodest thou among the sheepfolds , to hear the bleatings of the flocks ? For the divisions of Reuben \add there were\add* great searchings of heart.\f + \fr 5.16 \ft For: or, In\f*

Gilead abode beyond Jordan : and why did Dan remain in ships ? Asher continued on the sea shore , and abode in his breaches.\f + \fr 5.17 \ft shore: or, port\f*\f + \fr 5.17 \ft breaches: or, creeks\f*
Zebulun and Naphtali \add were\add* a people \add that\add* jeoparded their lives unto the death in the high places of the field.\f + \fr 5.18 \ft jeoparded: Heb. exposed to reproach\f*
The kings came \add and\add* fought , then fought the kings of Canaan in Taanach by the waters of Megiddo ; they took no gain of money.
They fought from heaven ; the stars in their courses fought against Sisera.\f + \fr 5.20 \ft courses: Heb. paths\f*
The river of Kishon swept them away , that ancient river , the river Kishon. O my soul , thou hast trodden down strength.
Then were the horsehoofs broken by the means of the pransings , the pransings of their mighty ones.\f + \fr 5.22 \ft pransings: or, tramplings, or, plungings\f*

Curse ye Meroz , said the angel of the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, curse ye bitterly the inhabitants thereof; because they came not to the help of the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, to the help of the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* against the mighty. \p
Blessed above women shall Jael the wife of Heber the Kenite be, blessed shall she be above women in the tent.
He asked water , \add and\add* she gave \add him\add* milk ; she brought forth butter in a lordly dish.

She put her hand to the nail , and her right hand to the workmen’s hammer ; and with the hammer she smote Sisera , she smote off his head , when she had pierced and stricken through his temples.\f + \fr 5.26 \ft with…: Heb. she hammered\f*
At her feet he bowed , he fell , he lay down : at her feet he bowed , he fell : where he bowed , there he fell down dead.\f + \fr 5.27 \ft At: Heb. Between\f*\f + \fr 5.27 \ft dead: Heb. destroyed\f*
The mother of Sisera looked out at a window , and cried through the lattice , Why is his chariot \add so\add* long in coming ? why tarry the wheels of his chariots ?
Her wise ladies answered her, yea, she returned answer to herself,\f + \fr 5.29 \ft answer: Heb. her words\f*

Have they not sped ? have they \add not\add* divided the prey ; to every man a damsel \add or\add* two ; to Sisera a prey of divers colours , a prey of divers colours of needlework , of divers colours of needlework on both sides , \add meet\add* for the necks of \add them that take\add* the spoil ?\f + \fr 5.30 \ft every…: Heb. the head of a man\f*

So let all thine enemies perish , O \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*: but \add let\add* them that love him \add be\add* as the sun when he goeth forth in his might. And the land had rest forty years.
